Package: countmissing
Title: Count missing values for all columns by group
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Andrea", "Wong Koo", , "andreawongkoo@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0009-3914-1533"))
Description: This package provides count_all_missing_by_group(), 
    a function to efficiently count missing values across all columns of a 
    data frame, grouped by a specified variable. Built with `dplyr`, 
    this function returns a summary table with one row per group level, 
    making it easy to assess missing data within grouped subsets. 
